commit_pushdown_eco(25.10)                          commit_pushdown_eco(25.10)

Name
       commit_pushdown_eco - Commits ECO for a partition block by applying ECO
       and generating a database for the block

Syntax
       commit_pushdown_eco

       [-help]

       -eco_object_dir <dirName>

       -post_eco_dir <dirName>

       -pre_eco_dir <dirName>

       [-ptns <ptnNameList>]

       Commits  ECO  for  a  partition  block by applying ECO and generating a
       database for the block. It applies the  previously  generated  ECO  ob-
       jects, to each partition, in parallel, using EDP (parallel/distributed)
       framework.

       Note: The commit_pushdown_eco command also commits the FlexHtree amend-
       ment  into the partition block. Clock amendments can be restored by us-
       ing the create_ccopt_clock_tree_spec command.

Parameters
       -eco_object_dir <dirName>
              Specifies the parent directory which contains all partition sub-
              directories in which ECO object files of partitions are kept.

              Note: The eco object file names are pre-determined to be:

              <eco_logical.txt>

              <eco_physical.txt>

              <eco_net.def.gz>

              <eco_pin.txt>

              Data_type: string, required

       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation for each commit_pushdown_eco parameter. For a detailed
              description  of  the  command and all of its parameters, use the
              man command: man commit_pushdown_eco.

       -post_eco_dir <dirName>
              Specifies the parent directory  in  which,  after  applying  the
              ECOs, the partition databases are to be saved.

              Default: <./post_eco_dir>

              Data_type: string, required

       -pre_eco_dir <dirName>
              Specifies  the  latest  version of original design, to which ECO
              objects need to be applied. It contains sub-directories to  rep-
              resent latest version of each partition database.

              Data_type: string, required

       -ptns <ptnNameList>
              Specifies  the list of partition names for which ECO objects are
              created.

              Data_type: string, optional

